The paper deals with 3D shape retrieval, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of bag of words approach and comparison with other methods suggests that the paper may also belong to machine learning (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The fact that the method can be applied to both rigid and articulated/deformable 3D models suggests that it may also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
